+# Playwright Kanban UI test suite
+
+This folder contains a Playwright-based test suite that exercises the Kanban UI using the **real backend** and the app's client-side auth approach.
+
+## Files
+
+- `fixtures.ts` — Playwright fixture that fetches the test user (from `PLAYWRIGHT_TEST_EMAIL`) and injects it into `localStorage` before navigation.
+- `helpers/seed.ts` — helpers to create tasks via `POST /api/tasks` and fetch tasks.
+- `helpers/drag.ts` — robust drag helper using Playwright's mouse API.
+- `kanban.full.spec.ts` — the full Kanban test suite (seed, drag, verify).
+- `playwright.config.cjs` — recommended Playwright config (root).
+
+## Environment variables
+
+- `PLAYWRIGHT_BASE_URL` — base URL for your dev server (default `http://localhost:3000`).
+- `PLAYWRIGHT_TEST_EMAIL` — email of the test user to use (default `dev@local`).
+
+## Run locally
+
+1. Start dev server:
+
+```bash
+export PLAYWRIGHT_BASE_URL="http://localhost:3000"
+export PLAYWRIGHT_TEST_EMAIL="dev@local"
+npm run dev
+```
+
+2. Run tests:
+
+```bash
+npx playwright test --config=playwright.config.cjs e2e/playwright/kanban.full.spec.ts --project=chromium --headed
+```
+
+## CI notes
+
+- The included GitHub Actions workflow is a template. If your CI needs DB seeding (to ensure `dev@local` exists), replace the placeholder `Seed DB` step with your seeding command or SQL.
+- If Playwright tests time out in CI, consider:
+  - increasing timeouts in `playwright.config.cjs`
+  - running headless in CI by setting `PLAYWRIGHT_HEADLESS=true` or setting `use.headless: true`
+
+## Troubleshooting
+
+- If the app's DOM selectors differ from the selectors in `kanban.full.spec.ts`, update the `SELECTORS` object at the top of the file.
+- If `seedTask` fails with 401 or 403, ensure the `x-user-data` header is accepted by your backend, and that the test user exists in the DB.
+- If drag doesn't move tasks reliably, increase `postDropMs` in `helpers/drag.ts` and/or increase `steps`.
+
+## Common failures & fixes
+
+- **User not found in /api/users**: Ensure `PLAYWRIGHT_TEST_EMAIL` matches a user. Create the user in DB or update the env var.
+- **POST /api/tasks returns 401**: Backend expects a different auth header. Confirm `x-user-data` is correct, or modify `seedTask` to send the header your backend expects.
+- **Selectors mismatch**: Update the `SELECTORS` map in `kanban.full.spec.ts`.
+
+If you want, I can adjust selectors to match your app exactly when you paste the relevant task item HTML snippet.
